Rating: 4
I read the previous reviews and made some modifications that worked out well. 1. the eggs should also be at room temperature. 2. Add two teaspoons of vanilla extract instead of one, along with 1/8 teaspoon of cinnamon. 3. Bake for 10 minutes at 350 degrees,if using a dark heavy cookie sheet. 4. Beating the shortening, butter and sugars until very light and fluffy is an excellent suggestion and should be followed. 5. Refridgerate the dough for 20-30 minutes. 6. After placing the balls of dough on the cookie sheet I pressed them with the bottom of a flat glass dipped in granulated sugar so they wouldn't stick to the glass. The combination of shortening and butter prevents the cookies from spreading. Great tasting cookies.

