I followed this recipe exactly - and I think that was part of the problem. It really does need to be tinkered with. I liked the consistency of the cookies (I wound up with rather flat cookies, crunchy on the outside, soft in the middle), but they are a bit cakey. The biggest problem I have is taste. They are very bland but I believe the taste could be improved with better ingredients. Here are my suggestions. Use high quality margarine and no white sugar at all. Refrigerate the dough for about 20 minutes before forming the cookies, and don't make the balls too big. Mine flattened out TOO much because the dough was room temperature when I put it into the oven. Of course one could argue that any recipe that needs so much tinkering is not worth trying to make again at all......

