These cookies are excellent. I followed the recipe exactly as written. I hate thin, flat chocolate chip cookies. These were perfectly puffy and shaped when they came out of the oven. They did sink slightly on cooling but they did not collapse. ALL INGREDIENTS WERE ROOM TEMPERATURE. I think this makes a difference. Also I really take it to heart when a recipe says mix until light and fluffy. I used a whisk attachment to whip the sugars, butter and butter flavored Crisco. I then switched to a mixing paddle (so as not to make the cookies tough by over mixing the flour mixture). Lastly I baked them in a 350* oven, middle rack exactly 12 minutes. PERFECTLY COOKED Just slightly brown. I should also note I make my cookies hearty I got about 27 cookies. I can't imagine people making small (60+) cookies and baking them for 12 minutes and not have them overcooked. Just my thoughts - hope they help.

